# No game file updates without permission

Do **not** create, modify, delete, or overwrite any files under the installed game directory unless the user explicitly asks to update/deploy/install into the game in that message (or clearly continues an approved deploy).

Typical game path:
`C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\Sovereign Syndicate\`

Includes (non-exhaustive): `Mods\`, `MelonLoader\`, `Sovereign Syndicate_Data\`, localization CSV, DLLs, `venv`, voice wav/refs/scripts inside Mods.

## Allowed without permission

- Edit project/repo sources (e.g. `IdeaProjects\Sovereign-Syndicate-RU-Audio`, workspace copies)
- Build artifacts **inside the repo** (`bin\`, etc.)
- Read-only inspection of game files

## When the user says to update the game

1. Follow `.cursor/rules/game-file-backup.mdc` (fresh backup under `C:\Temp\SovereignSyndicateBackup\`)
2. Deploy only what was requested
3. Confirm backup path and what was written

## Examples

```
// ❌ User: "пофикси паузы в озвучке"
// → fix repo only; do NOT copy DLL/scripts into Mods

// ✅ User: "обнови файлы в игре"
// → backup, then deploy
```
